5000|$|The {{following}} <b>Grand</b> <b>Lodges</b> {{were formed}} by pre-existing [...] "Time Immemorial" [...] lodges (lodges that predated {{the concept of}} having <b>Grand</b> <b>Lodges</b> to supervise and coordinate the craft, and thus were retained as having existed from [...] "time immemorial").|$|R
50|$|The Knights and Ladies of Honor were {{organized}} on a three tier system with local Subordinate <b>Lodges,</b> state level <b>Grand</b> <b>Lodges</b> and {{governed by a}} national Supreme Lodge. There were 16 <b>Grand</b> <b>Lodges</b> in 1896. Its headquarters was in Indianapolis, Indiana.|$|R
50|$|Throughout the US {{there are}} also {{numerous}} bodies that claim to be Masonic <b>Lodges</b> and <b>Grand</b> <b>Lodges,</b> but which are not recognized as such by UGLE, the mainstream <b>Grand</b> <b>Lodges,</b> nor their Prince Hall counterparts. These are deemed to be irregular.|$|R
